All Classes

  • Class Description
    BinarySearch
    Generic binary search algorithm with support for and beyond sorted lists and arrays, in a fluent API.
    BinarySearch.DoubleSearchTarget
    Represents the search target that can be found through bisecting the double domain.
    BinarySearch.IntSearchTarget
    Represents the search target that can be found through bisecting the integer domain.
    BinarySearch.LongSearchTarget
    Represents the search target that can be found through bisecting the long integer domain.
    BinarySearch.Table<K,​C extends java.lang.Comparable<C>>
    Like a hash table, allows looking up comparable values by a key, except the lookup is through binary search instead of hashing.
    CaseBreaker
    Utility to break and convert input strings (normally identifier strings) in camelCase, UpperCamelCase, snake_case, UPPER_SNAKE_CASE and dash-case etc.
    GoogleSql
    Facade class providing SafeQuery templates for GoogleSQL.
    GuavaCollectors
    Guava-specific Collectors and BiCollectors.
    Immutables
    Convenient factory methods of common immutable Guava data types that are concise yet unambiguous when static imported.
    InsertionPoint<C extends java.lang.Comparable<C>>
    An insertion point in a sequence of elements (normally of indexes), which is either an exact element, or in between two adjacent elements in a discrete domain, or before or after all elements of the discrete domain.
    SafeQuery
    Facade class to generate queries based on a string template in the syntax of StringFormat, with compile-time guard rails and runtime protection against SQL injection and programmer mistakes.
